- "Big-budget films" refers to movies with a budget greater than $250 million;
- "High average rating" means an average rating greater than 5;
- The rating values are converted to numeric by removing decimal points before averaging.

- "Top-rated" implies the highest average rating;
- "Considering both their ratings and the number of reviews" means that movies with higher ratings and more reviews are preferred;
- "Genres" refers to the categories or types of movies, such as Action, Drama, or Comedy.

- "bloomed in the cinematic garden of 2007" refers to movies released in 2007;
- "shining brightly in the eyes of users in 2022" refers to user ratings given in 2022;
- "average rating that surpasses the mark of 7" refers to an average user rating greater than 7.

- "shining stars" refers to movies with a rating higher than the average rating of their genre;
- "average brilliance of their genres" refers to the average rating of movies within the same genre;
- "box office haul" refers to the total revenue generated by the movies.

- "Top 5 films" refers to the films with the highest average ratings;
- "Captivated the hearts of viewers" refers to movies that have received high ratings from users;
- "Most glowing review" refers to the highest-rated review for each movie.

- 'top-rated' refers to movies with the highest average ratings;
- The ranking is based on the average ratings in descending order;
- Only the top 10 movies are considered.
